13 DEPENDENCY-NEGLECT REPRESENTATION APPROPRIATION TRANSFER AUTHORITY. The
14 Administrative Office of the Courts shall receive approval from the Chief
15 Fiscal Officer of the State and Arkansas Legislative Council or Joint Budget
16 Committee to transfer funds and appropriations between line items Regular
17 Salaries, Personal Services Matching, Operating Expense, Professional Fees
18 and Attorney Ad Litem Fees/Reimbursements of the Division of Dependency-
19 Neglect Representation appropriation herein for the payment of employees
20 and/or contractors providing legal services for the Division of Dependency-
21 Neglect Representation.
22 Determining the maximum number of employees and the maximum amount of
23 appropriation and general revenue funding for a state agency each fiscal year
24 is the prerogative of the General Assembly. This is usually accomplished by
25 delineating such maximums in the appropriation act(s) for a state agency and
26 the general revenue allocations authorized for each fund and fund account by
27 amendment to the Revenue Stabilization law. Further, the General Assembly
28 has determined that the Administrative Office of the Courts may operate more
29 efficiently if some flexibility is provided to the Administrative Office of
30 the Courts authorizing broad powers under this Section. Therefore, it is
31 both necessary and appropriate that the General Assembly maintain oversight
32 by requiring prior approval of the Legislative Council or Joint Budget
33 Committee as provided by this section. The requirement of approval by the
34 Legislative Council or Joint Budget Committee is not a severable part of this
35 section. If the requirement of approval by the Legislative Council or Joint
36 Budget Committee is ruled unconstitutional by a court of competent
18 04-07-2025 17:31:37 JAR037
As Engrossed: S4/7/25 SB72
1 jurisdiction, this entire section is void.
2 The provisions of this section shall be in effect only from July 1, 2024
3 2025 through June 30, 2025 2026.
